public abstract class Deck<C extends Card<? extends Suit<?>,? extends Rank<?>>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<C>

Encapsulates the notion of a deck of cards of a given type. This may be specified by subclasses or deferred until declaration, whichever is more convenient to use in implementation. A deck is a sort of pseudo-Collection that subclasses are to fill with an initial state. This abstract class facilitates construction by initializing the underlying structure of cards as empty, nothing further. Decks may function as a FIFO or LIFO queue, and subclasses should take care to specify which is to be created.

Author:
Tor E Hagemann
